xediaVlanMIB.name: xediaVlanMIB
xediaVlanMIB.description: This module defines objects for management of Xedia's support for VLANs and 802.1p and 802.1q Ethernet tagged frames.

xVlanIDTable.name: xVlanIDTable
xVlanIDTable.description: A table of VLAN IDs configured on Ethernet subinterfaces.

xVlanIDEntry.name: xVlanIDEntry
xVlanIDEntry.description: An association between an Ethernet subinterface and a VLAN ID.

xVlanID.name: xVlanID
xVlanID.description: The 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

xVlanConfigTable.name: xVlanConfigTable
xVlanConfigTable.description: A table of configuration information applicable to VLANs indexed by Ethernet physical (integral) interface.

xVlanConfigEntry.name: xVlanConfigEntry
xVlanConfigEntry.description: VLAN configuration information for a particular Ethernet physical (integral) interface.

xVlanConfigAdmitTaggedFrames.name: xVlanConfigAdmitTaggedFrames
xVlanConfigAdmitTaggedFrames.description: Whether 802.1q/802.1p tagged frames will be received by the box. If this value is false, the frames will be dropped.

xVlanConfigAdmitConfiguredVlansOnly.name: xVlanConfigAdmitConfiguredVlansOnly
xVlanConfigAdmitConfiguredVlansOnly.description: Whether only those 802.1q tagged frames that contain a VLAN ID that has been configured on the box will be received. If this value is true, frames from VLANs with other VLAN IDs will be dropped. This variable does not apply to bridged traffic.

xVlanConfigStripBridgedTags.name: xVlanConfigStripBridgedTags
xVlanConfigStripBridgedTags.description: Whether 802.1q/802.1p tagged frames that are being bridged will have the tag stripped out of the packet before it is forwarded. This variable does not apply to routed traffic.

xVlanConfigGVRP.name: xVlanConfigGVRP
xVlanConfigGVRP.description: Whether the GVRP protocol for dynamically informing the network of the VLAN IDs configured in the box is enabled.

xVlanConfigGARPJoinTime.name: xVlanConfigGARPJoinTime
xVlanConfigGARPJoinTime.description: The GARP Join time, in centiseconds. This variable is a component of the GVRP protocol.

xVlanCompliance.name: xVlanCompliance
xVlanCompliance.description: The compliance statement for all agents that support this MIB. A compliant agent implements all objects defined in this MIB.

xVlanGroup.name: xVlanGroup
xVlanGroup.description: The set of all accessible objects in this MIB.
